<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Capture a change in pressure for a single pressure set. UnitInc may be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// expressed in terms of upward or downward pressure depending on the client</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Pressure increments are tiny, typically 1-2 units, and this is only for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// heuristics, so we don&#39;t check UnitInc overflow. Instead, we may have a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// higher level assert that pressure is consistent within a region. We also</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// effectively ignore dead defs which don&#39;t affect heuristics much.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="102" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pressurechange"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pressurechange/#a8cc3404c1d3dfcbccbd103421f1e5a59">PressureChange</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Track the current register pressure at some position in the instruction</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="343"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// stream, and remember the high water mark within the region traversed. This</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="344"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// does not automatically consider live-through ranges. The client may</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="349"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// each block boundary and explicitly adjusting pressure to account for block</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="350"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// live-in and live-out register sets.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="351"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="352"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// RegPressureTracker holds a reference to a RegisterPressure result that it</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="353"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// computes incrementally. During downward tracking, P.BottomIdx or P.BottomPos</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="354"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// is invalid until it reaches the end of the block or closeRegion() is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="355"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// explicitly called. Similarly, P.TopIdx is invalid during upward</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00356" /><CodeLine lineNumber="356"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// tracking. Changing direction has the side effect of closing region, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00357" /><CodeLine lineNumber="357"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// traversing past TopIdx or BottomIdx reopens it.</span></CodeLine>
